\mathcal{L}\{f(t)\}=\int_{0^-}^{\infty}e^{-st}f(t)dt
=\left[\frac{f(t)e^{-st}}{-s}\right]_{0^-}^{\infty}-\int_{0^-}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-st}}{-s}f'(t)dt\space,\space\space\space(by\space parts)
=\left[-\frac{f(0^-)}{-s}\right]+\frac{1}{s}\mathcal{L}\{f'(t)\}
t\to\infty
Re(s)>0
